# Sanity CMS Migration Path

The entire codebase is structured so that migrating to Sanity CMS requires **only changing the data import on each page** — components and types remain untouched.

## The Migration Change (Per Page)

```ts
// BEFORE (static file)
import { homePageData } from '@/lib/data/pages/home'

// AFTER (Sanity fetch) — one line change, everything else identical
const homePageData = await sanityFetch<HomePage>({ query: HOME_PAGE_QUERY })
```

## Why This Works

1. **Types already match Sanity schema** — use `_key` on array items, nested objects, reference shapes
2. **Components are pure** — they only receive props, so the data source is irrelevant to them
3. **Pages already async** — App Router pages are async Server Components; adding `await` is zero friction

## Designing Types for Sanity Compatibility

```ts
// ✅ Sanity-ready — _key on array items, nested objects mirror document schema
export interface ServiceItem {
  _key: string          // required for Sanity array items
  title: string
  description: string
  image: {
    asset: { url: string; alt: string }   // mirrors Sanity image reference
  }
}

// ❌ Not Sanity-ready — flat arrays with no _key, mismatched shape
export interface ServiceItem {
  id: number            // use _key instead
  img: string           // Sanity images are objects, not strings
}
```

## Folder Boundary to Preserve

Keep this separation clean — **never blur the boundary**:

| Layer | Role | Changes at migration? |
|---|---|---|
| `lib/types/` | Shared interfaces | No |
| `lib/data/` | Static content source | Replaced by `sanityFetch()` |
| `lib/seo/` | Metadata helpers | No |
| `components/` | Presentation | No |
| `app/**/page.tsx` | Imports data, renders | Import line only |

## Never Do Before Migration

- Do not create component-level data fetching — it breaks the migration path
- Do not use `id: number` — use `_key: string` to match Sanity
- Do not store image URLs as plain strings — use `{ asset: { url, alt } }` shape
